<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Sarah Armstrong – Written evidence</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Sarah Armstrong – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I am writing in support of the Green Lanes Protection Group, members of the House of Lords and others who are requesting that the Bill be amended to include additional rights of way clauses which would have the following effect:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">classify as restricted byways all unsealed unclassified roads (UUCRs) (</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ie</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> green lanes)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">downgrade all existing unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs) to restricted byway status</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">OR, or if this is seen as too draconian a measure, downgrade to restricted byway all unsealed UUCRs and BOATs in National Parks, Areas of Natural Beauty (AONBs) and where part of National Trails </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">provide</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> rights of appeal against refusals by highway authorities to make Traffic Regulation Orders excluding motor vehicles from </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">unsurfaced</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> lanes.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I live in central Sheffield and walk with my family on the hills at the edge of the city and in the Peak District most weekends. In addition, I have over the last 20 years spent a great deal of time in and around the Peak District village of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Eyam</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> where my mother lives.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">When my children were small we would regularly take them in prams, pushchairs, and later on foot, around </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Eyam</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, where a number of green lanes provided safe and pleasant passage away from motorised traffic. In recent years these lanes have become popular with off-road motor bikers, to the extent that some are now so eroded that my elderly mother can no longer use them. One has been mended up with hard-core and gravel, and since the ground slopes steeply it is treacherous underfoot in all weathers – I hesitate to walk on it myself. In addition to this is the constant worry that a group of motorbikes will suddenly hurtle up at speed. I certainly would not feel safe taking young children on the lanes these days, and I am amazed – given the numbers of school parties that visit </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Eyam</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> throughout the year to study the plague memorials on one of these lanes - that the law allows the bikers continued access. It is surely only a matter of time before there is a serious accident at </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Eyam</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">There are two main routes on the hills around Sheffield which have become popular with motor bikers and off-roaders. Both of these had become seriously eroded and virtually no-go areas by non-motor users. One of these has recently been closed to motor vehicles, and after repair is now once more used by a great many people. Walkers continue to avoid the other.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">As users of our green lanes the off-roaders and motor </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">bikers</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> are in a small minority, yet they terrorise the majority and cause expensive damage to the environment which we all have to pay for. We therefore ask you to accept the changes to the draft Deregulation Bill which are being suggested by the Green Lanes Environmental Action Group and others.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">10 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>